latestPosts.caption:
To the little one who came into my life three years ago, do you remember the first day we met? You were such a tiny, energetic ball of fluff, full of life and excitement. Yes I was nervous and scared, but I couldn’t wait to take you home. Since that day, my life has been nothing but magical because I had found a forever companion in you. From then on, everything I did was just focused around giving you the best life I could. Whether it was taking you on walks, sitting by the road watching the world go by, introducing you to my friends, traveling together, cleaning you up every day, feeding you, or even scolding you when you didn’t listen—oh, we were just living the perfect life. Your happiness and the joy in your smile were the moments I cherished the most.

Maadhu, even though you're no longer physically here with us, I know you're still watching over us. Not a single moment goes by without you on my mind. Everywhere I look, I still feel your presence, as if you're right here with me. You were, and always will be, the best, my child. You left us too soon, but as they say, "Great lives are short, but they leave a lasting legacy." You've touched the hearts of everyone you've met.

Happy birthday, my boy. While we couldn’t do our usual birthday photoshoot or take our special trip to Munnar, I hope you're enjoying your favorite treats, ice cream, and making lots of new friends. Stay happy, my superstar. I can’t wait until we meet again so I can shower you with endless kisses and cuddles. See you soon. 🕊♥️🫂

latestPosts.caption:
To my boy, whom I loved deeply,
I’m so sorry I couldn’t save you. I’m sorry for all the pain you had to endure. Please know you were the only one I truly loved with all my heart. You were the best boy. ♥️
Three years ago, when we brought you home, everyone warned us about getting a Chow Chow—they said you’d be aggressive. But you proved them all wrong. You grew up to be the most loyal and loving companion to your family. 🫶
Maaadhu, my heart is shattered, my boy. My life will never be the same without you. I feel so lost, like I have no one left and no purpose to hold onto. I dreamed of taking you to so many places, of giving you so many more adventures. But you left too soon. You deserved so much more time, but life has been cruel to us.
You were a star, Maadhu. Everywhere you went, people couldn’t help but take pictures of you, and you always posed like the sweetest boy. It filled me with so much pride to be your pet parent—it was truly an honor to call you mine. 
Please know that your family loves you deeply, and you are truly irreplaceable. There will always be an emptiness in our lives without you here. 
I miss you my boy and see you on the other side, very soon! 🫂🕊💗
(20/11/2021- 08/01/2025)
